{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Moghadam et al. [66] observed that GGBFS replacements improved sulfate and chloride resistance, enhancing long-term durability.",
    "Zou et al. [67] reported a 15% increase in compressive strength and a 12-15% improvement in overall performance with a 30% GGBFS replacement.",
    "Chi et al. [68] demonstrated gains in compressive strength at 20% and 40% replacement levels, though strength slightly decreased at 60%.",
    "Cleetus et al. [69] found improvements in elasticity and flexural strength at 20% replacement, with additional benefits at higher levels.",
    "Cahyani and Rusdianto [70] noted that GGBFS maintained compressive strength comparable to conventional concrete up to a 50% replacement, with minimal reductions beyond that."
  ]
}